All items below have been implemented.

1. [DONE] Separate UIs for vendor and customer based on logins.
   - New /login route with Customer / Vendor tabs.
   - Role + vendor selection persisted in zustand.
   - Header shows different nav per role (vendor sees Dashboard only, no cart).
   - Route guards redirect appropriately:
       /vendor                 -> requires vendor role (else /login)
       /cart, /quick-order,
       /vendors/$vendorId      -> vendors are bounced to /vendor
       /orders, /orders/:id    -> require any signed-in customer
   1.1 [DONE] Vendor manually accepts orders (Accept / Decline buttons on the
       Pending stage; status no longer auto-advances).
   1.2 [DONE] Vendor dashboard upgraded: open/close toggle, today's revenue,
       counts (To Accept / Preparing / Ready), order notes panel, decline
       option, sequential order numbers, vendor-name banner.
   1.3 [DONE] Customer vs vendor UIs differentiated by header label
       ("Vendor Console" vs "GIKI · Eat fast"), nav, redirects, available
       actions, and styling.

2. [DONE] Responsive design: mobile-first throughout (hamburger menu,
   wrapping order rows, card stacks on small screens, smaller paddings).

3. [DONE] Progress bar is updated in real time by the vendor.
   - Removed the demo setTimeout that auto-advanced the customer's order.
   - Vendor's "Mark X" / "Accept" buttons are the only way to progress.
   - Cross-tab sync: a window 'storage' listener calls
     useApp.persist.rehydrate() so a customer page in another tab/device
     reflects the vendor's update without refresh.

4. [DONE] Time problems
   4.1 12-hour format everywhere (format12, formatDate12 helpers). Vendor
       dashboard, cart, orders list, order detail, header clock all use
       "h:mm AM/PM".
   4.2 Real-time clock visible in the header (refreshes every 30 s) and a
       useNow() hook drives "x min ago" labels on the order detail page.
   4.3 Pickup time is suggested automatically from the queue
       (suggestedPickupForVendor uses the vendor's prep time + queue depth),
       and the cart's <input type="time"> has min={suggested}. Manual
       attempts to pick an earlier time are clamped + show a toast.

5. [DONE] Extra instructions textarea added to cart (240-char limit) and
   surfaced on the order detail and the vendor dashboard.
   5.1 Sequential order numbers (orderCounter starts at 1001, persisted).

6. [DONE] Footer no longer says "Built for CS272 · Milestone 3" — replaced
   with "Skip the queue · Eat on time".
